This paper deals with trust establishment and advisory in mobile networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also addresses security breaches in the Internet, which is a sub-topic of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of encounter frequency, duration, behavior vectors and matrices to establish trust involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI). The evaluation of DTN routing in mobile peer-to-peer networks using trust and selfishness models involves the study of algorithms and data structures, which is a sub-topic of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the dynamics in wireless mobile networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
